<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>She never fails to turn heads when it comes to her sense of style.</p>

<p>And Kelly Brook cut a chic figure as she arrived to work at Heart radio in London's Global Studios on Thursday.</p>

<p>The presenter, 40, kept warm in a cosy brown roll neck jumper and a brown satin skirt as she cheerfully made her way down the street.</p>

<p>Here she is: Kelly Brook cut a chic figure as she arrived to work at Heart radio in London's Global Studios on Thursday</p>

<p>Adding a casual element to her autumnal outfit, Kelly donned a pair of white trainers.</p>

<p>While she accessorised her look with oversized black sunglasses and carried her essentials in a quilted black handbag. </p>

<p>The TV personality kept her hairstyle simple, opting to swept her brunette tresses into a ponytail, while she added a minimal palette of make-up.</p>

<p>Kelly was clearly full of the joys of autumn as she flashed a warm smile before making her way inside. </p>

<p>Looking good: The presenter, 40, kept warm in a cosy brown roll neck jumper and a brown satin skirt as she cheerfully made her way down the street</p>

<p>Kelly's outing comes as she admitted she's 'not worried' about her 'weight creeping up'.</p>

<p>She also declared 'diets shouldn't be about deprivation', after revealing she shed a whopping two stone in March.</p>

<p>While she has been keeping busy by exercising at home, her diet consists of 'healthy, low-calorie meals' with sweet treats such as popcorn and homemade fruit lollies.</p>

<p>The brunette has been candid about her weight fluctuating, with the bombshell slimming down to a size 10-12 after going to a size 16.</p>

<p>Low-key look: Adding a casual element to her autumnal outfit, Kelly donned a pair of white trainers</p>

<p>Radiant: The TV personality kept her hairstyle simple, opting to swept her brunette tresses into a ponytail, while she added a minimal palette of make-up</p>

<p>On her current figure, she told new! magazine: 'I'm a real foodie and enjoy cooking. I wasn't surprised at all to see my weight creep up a little over the last few weeks.</p>

<p>'[I've gained] a few pounds, but I'm not worried. I know I can lean on the SlimFast 3.2.1. Plan to deal with my weight loss ups and downs, so I can get back on track.</p>

<p>'It's easy and it works. Diets shouldn't be about deprivation - they need to be sustainable after all.'</p>

<p>Cheerful: Kelly was clearly full of the joys of autumn as she flashed a warm smile before making her way inside</p>
